      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Q2. Monk (related to top ten, item 1): Is it correct that the &amp;quot;strikethrough&amp;quot; focus effect does not actaully stop you taking damage on a successful strikethrough of a riposte ? &lt;em&gt;At the moment, you can strikethrough a block/dodge, but if you striketrhough a riposte (successfully) the mob STILL gets to attack you and can hit you (and if this is a boss mob, thats often 4k + damage !).&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A2. Strikethrough is essentially an ability that allows you to strike through your opponents best efforts to defend against your attack -- Riposte is basically a simultaneous offensive / defensive action. Strikethrough is allowing the monks to bypass the defensive portion of that action, but it does not allow them to completely evade the offensive portion of the action.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
